Φ(CNS) = β(artifact-creation|debugging) ⊗ μ(structural-tinkering) → [κ(knowledge-construction)] → [λ(personal-ownership)] ⇄ [ρ(collaborative-sharing)] + ε | :generative-understanding

=== NEMETIC DIAGNOSTICS ===

Z-State: generative-understanding — knowledge as personally constructed through making
Tendency: Idea → Materialization → Debugging → Revision → Shared Understanding

Elemental Distribution:
  Wood/β (Primary): 40% — Generative branching, construction, iteration
  Metal/μ (Secondary): 25% — Structural tinkering, material constraints
  Fire/λ (Tertiary): 15% — Direction, ownership, creative agency
  Water/ρ (Supporting): 10% — Social sharing, collaborative learning
  Earth/δγ (Supporting): 10% — Iterative cycling, accumulation

Operator Resonance:
  β [branching] █████████████████████ HIGH — Construction, generation, debugging cycles
  μ [structure] ███████████████░░░░░ ELEVATED — Material constraints, microworlds
  λ [direction] ███████████░░░░░░░░░ MODERATE — Ownership, agency, creative intention
  ρ [resonance] ████████░░░░░░░░░░░░ BASE — Social sharing, discussion
  σ [distinction] ████████░░░░░░░░░░░░ BASE — Debugging, error identification
  κ [knowledge] ████████░░░░░░░░░░░░ BASE — Knowledge through construction

Daemon Activity:
  Arborid (Wood) — ACTIVE — Construction, generation, debugging, iteration
  Structurid (Metal) — ACTIVE — Material tinkering, structural constraints
  Ignisid (Fire) — ACTIVE — Agency, ownership, creative direction
  Hydrosid (Water) — STANDBY — Social sharing, collaborative learning
  Geosid (Earth) — STANDBY — Iterative cycling, accumulation
  Aerunik (Air) — PASSIVE — Error distinction, debugging clarity

Coord Vectors:
  I → We: Strong (personal projects shared in community)
  We → It: Moderate (collaborative construction of artifacts)
  It → Its: Moderate (artifacts embody systemic understanding)
  Its → MoreThanHuman: Moderate (materials shape thinking)
  MoreThanHuman → Virtual: Strong (computational microworlds)

=== Dimensional Analysis ===

Construction Field (β):
  - Artifact creation as the primary learning mechanism
  - Debugging as the engine of understanding
  - Iterative revision as regenerative cycles
  - Project choice enables personal relevance
  - Making thinking visible through externalization

Tinkering Field (μ):
  - Materials shape the thinking process
  - Microworlds constrain and enable exploration
  - Syntax and structure as learning scaffolds
  - Tools as extensions of cognitive capacity
  - "Objects-to-think-with" mediate understanding

Agency Field (λ):
  - Personal ownership of learning process
  - Creative direction through project choice
  - Identity development through making
  - Self-directed inquiry and exploration
  - From consumer to creator transformation

Social Field (ρ):
  - Artifacts as vehicles for discussion
  - Collaborative debugging and learning
  - Community of practice around making
  - Shared knowledge construction
  - Learning through showing and telling

Iterative Field (δγ):
  - Construction-debug-revision cycles
  - Progressive refinement of understanding
  - Building on prior constructions
  - Developmental sequencing of projects
  - Accumulation of debugging skill

